TY  - JOUR
AU  - Heyerdahl-Larsen, Christian
AU  - Walden, Johan
T1  - Distortions and Efficiency in Production Economies with Heterogeneous Beliefs
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab068
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 35
IS  - 4
SP  - 1775
EP  - 1812
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study consumption, savings, and asset prices in economies with disagreement and production, focusing on settings with real effects of disagreement. Aggregate savings may be significantly distorted under disagreement, possibly related to the undersaving puzzle. In the production economy, mispricing mainly manifests itself in idiosyncratic risk, in contrast to the exchange economy, where the risk-free rate and expected return on the market may be distorted. Potential policy implications include the introduction of investment taxes or subsidies. Our results highlight the real effects of disagreement in financial markets, and the differences between economies with and without production.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab068
ER  - 



