TY  - JOUR
AU  - Cornaggia, Kimberly
AU  - Hund, John
AU  - Nguyen, Giang
AU  - Ye, Zihan
T1  - Opioid Crisis Effects on Municipal Finance
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab066
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 35
IS  - 4
SP  - 2019
EP  - 2066
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We investigate the effects of opioid abuse on municipal finance. We employ instrumental variables, border discontinuity difference-in-differences regressions, and coarsened exact matching to identify consistent causal effects, while controlling for variation in economic conditions and demographics. Opioid abuse lowers credit ratings, increases new offer yields, and reduces bond issuance. Reversal of these effects following effective antiopioid legislation further supports causality. Differential effects due to investor heterogeneity suggest that opioid abuse affects municipal finance through a capital supply channel. Overall, we conclude that local opioid abuse impedes municipalities’ access to capital and thus hurts their ability to provide public services and infrastructure.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab066
ER  - 



