TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bansal, Ravi
AU  - Wu, Di (Andrew)
AU  - Yaron, Amir
T1  - Socially Responsible Investing in Good and Bad Times
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab072
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 35
IS  - 4
SP  - 2067
EP  - 2099
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We investigate the time variability of abnormal returns from socially responsible investing (SRI). Using portfolio regressions and event studies on multiple data sources, including analyst ratings, firm announcements, and realized incidents, we find that highly rated SRI stocks outperform lowly rated SRI stocks during good economic times, for example, periods with high market valuations or aggregate consumption, but underperform during bad times, such as recessions. This variation in abnormal returns of high-SR stocks vis-à-vis low SR stocks is consistent with a wealth-dependent investor preference for SR stocks that leads to an increased (decreased) demand for SRI during good (bad) times.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab072
ER  - 



